#
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import statsmodels.api as sm
import statsmodels.formula.api as smf
from plotnine import *
from datetime import datetime
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
# 
stock_data = pd.read_csv("sp500_45.csv")
stock_data.head()
# filter
##   ticker    ref.date  price.open  ...  price.low  price.high      volume
## 0    ACN  2001-07-19       15.10  ...      15.00       15.29  34994300.0
## 1    ACN  2001-07-20       15.05  ...      14.80       15.05   9238500.0
## 2    ACN  2001-07-23       15.00  ...      14.55       15.01   7501000.0
## 3    ACN  2001-07-24       14.95  ...      14.70       14.97   3537300.0
## 4    ACN  2001-07-25       14.70  ...      14.65       14.95   4208100.0
## 
## [5 rows x 8 columns]
MSFT = stock_data[stock_data['ticker']=='MSFT']
# select
p_MSFT = MSFT[['ref.date','price.close']]. \
    rename(columns={'ref.date':'date'}). \
    reset_index(drop=True)
p_MSFT['date']=pd.to_datetime(p_MSFT['date'])
p_MSFT.head()
#
##         date  price.close
## 0 1997-12-29    15.789063
## 1 1997-12-30    16.281250
## 2 1997-12-31    16.156250
## 3 1998-01-02    16.390625
## 4 1998-01-05    16.296875
sp500_index = pd.read_csv("sp500_index.csv")
p_SP500 = sp500_index[['ref.date','price.close']]. \
    rename(columns={'ref.date':'date'}). \
    reset_index(drop=True)
p_SP500['date']=pd.to_datetime(p_SP500['date'])
p_SP500.head()
# merge (join)
##         date  price.close
## 0 1997-12-29   953.349976
## 1 1997-12-30   970.840027
## 2 1997-12-31   970.429993
## 3 1998-01-02   975.039978
## 4 1998-01-05   977.070007
data_daily=pd.merge(p_SP500,p_MSFT,how='inner',on='date').\
    rename(columns={'price.close_x':'p_SP500','price.close_y':'p_MSFT'})
# filter time
data_daily = data_daily[(data_daily['date']>='1997-12-31') & \
                            (data_daily['date']<='2018-12-31')] 
data_daily['year'] = data_daily['date'].dt.year
data_daily['month'] = data_daily['date'].dt.month
# mutate
data_daily['l_MSFT']=data_daily['p_MSFT'].map(lambda x:np.log(x))
data_daily['l_SP500']=data_daily['p_SP500'].map(lambda x:np.log(x))
# ggplot en Python
(ggplot(data_daily) + geom_line(aes('date','p_MSFT'), size = 0.5) + scale_y_continuous(expand = [0.01,0.01],limits = [0,120]) 
+ labs(y = "Precio de las acciones de Microsoft (US $)",x= "Date (day)") + theme_bw())
## <ggplot: (8771328882710)>

plt.show()

(ggplot(data_daily) + geom_line(aes('date','p_SP500'), size = 0.5) + scale_y_continuous(expand = [0.01,0.01]) 
+ labs(y = "Índice S&P 500 del mercado bursátil",x= "Date (day)") + theme_bw())
## <ggplot: (-9223363265540286148)>

plt.show()
# mutate

data_daily['l.p_MSFT'] = data_daily['p_MSFT'].shift()
data_daily['l.p_SP500'] = data_daily['p_SP500'].shift()
data_daily['d.p_MSFT'] = data_daily['p_MSFT'] - data_daily['l.p_MSFT']
data_daily['d.p_SP500'] = data_daily['p_SP500'] - data_daily['l.p_SP500']
data_daily['r_MSFT'] = data_daily['d.p_MSFT']/data_daily['l.p_MSFT']*100
data_daily['r_SP500'] = data_daily['d.p_SP500']/data_daily['l.p_SP500']*100
data_daily.head()
##         date     p_SP500     p_MSFT  ...  d.p_SP500    r_MSFT   r_SP500
## 2 1997-12-31  970.429993  16.156250  ...        NaN       NaN       NaN
## 3 1998-01-02  975.039978  16.390625  ...   4.609985  1.450677  0.475046
## 4 1998-01-05  977.070007  16.296875  ...   2.030029 -0.571973  0.208200
## 5 1998-01-06  966.580017  16.390625  ... -10.489990  0.575264 -1.073617
## 6 1998-01-07  964.000000  16.195313  ...  -2.580017 -1.191608 -0.266922
## 
## [5 rows x 13 columns]
(ggplot(data_daily,aes('r_SP500','r_MSFT')) + geom_point() + geom_smooth(method='lm',se=False) + labs(x="Rendimiento diario del índice S&P 500 (%)",y="Rendimiento diario de Microsoft (%)") + theme_bw())

# regress

reg = smf.ols('r_MSFT ~ r_SP500', data=data_daily).fit()
print(reg.summary())
